{{Infobox animanga/Footer}}
{{Nihongo|'''''Descending Stories: Showa Genroku Rakugo Shinju'''''|昭和元禄落語心中|Shōwa Genroku Rakugo Shinjū| lit. "[[Shōwa period|Shōwa]], [[Genroku]], [[Rakugo]], and [[Shinjū|Double Suicide]]"}} is a Japanese [[manga]] series written and illustrated by Haruko Kumota. It began serialization in [[Kodansha]]'s ''ITAN'' magazine in 2010.<ref name="OAD1"/> The manga is licensed in North America by [[Kodansha USA]]. The manga was adapted into two [[original video animation]]s which were bundled with special editions of the seventh and eighth manga volumes on March 6 and August 7, 2015, respectively.<ref name="OAD1">{{cite web |url= http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-08-06/showa-genroku-rakugo-shinju-manga-gets-original-anime-dvd/.77349|title= Shōwa Genroku Rakugo Shinjū Manga Gets Original Anime DVD|date= 6 August 2014|accessdate= 16 November 2014|work= [[Anime News Network]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Historical Manga Shōwa Genroku Rakugo Shinjū Gets TV Anime, 2nd OAD|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2014-12-04/historical-manga-showa-genroku-rakugo-shinju-gets-tv-anime-2nd-oad/.81756|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=27 December 2015}}</ref> It was also adapted into an [[anime]] television series which aired between January 9, 2016 and April 2, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-12-16/showa-genroku-rakugo-shinju-tv-anime-video-previews-opening-song/.96533|title=Shōwa Genroku Rakugo Shinjū TV Anime's Video Reveals January 8 Debut|work=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=27 December 2015}}</ref> A second season of the anime television series aired between January 7, 2017 and March 25, 2017.<ref name="S2AirDate"/> A live-action series adaptation is scheduled to premiere on October 12, 2018.<ref name="DramaSeriesAnc"/> 

==Plot==
A man is released from prison and becomes the apprentice of a famous [[rakugo]] performer. The story focuses on the backstories of the performers and their struggle to gain popularity. Whilst learning he befriends another performer who has a completely different style.

==Characters==

===Main characters===
;{{Nihongo|Eighth Generation Yakumo Yurakutei|八代目 有楽亭 八雲|Hachidaime Yūrakutei Yakumo}} / {{Nihongo|Kikuhiko|菊比古}}
:{{anime voices|[[Akira Ishida]]}}
:Played by: [[Masaki Okada]]
:A rakugo storyteller known for his perfectionist style of rakugo. His birth name is never specified, although Sukeroku took to call him "Bon". He was given the name "'''Kikuhiko'''" when he became a student of the Seventh Generation Yakumo. He was originally a dancer, but he ruined his leg in an accident and ended up being given to Yakumo. During his time as a student, he would struggle to find his own rakugo having placed too much emphasis on flawless execution, but he was able to find inspiration thanks to Sukeroku. He would go on to inherit the Yakumo name, but initially he refused thinking that he was not worthy of it. Following the deaths of Sukeroku and Miyokichi, he inherited the name to fulfill Sukeroku's vision of keeping rakugo going in a time where tastes in entertainment change. He would later on become the head of the rakugo association.
;{{Nihongo|Second Generation Sukeroku Yurakutei|二代目 有楽亭 助六|Nidaime Yūrakutei Sukeroku}} / {{Nihongo|Hatsutaro|初太郎|Hatsutarō}}
:{{anime voices|[[Koichi Yamadera]]}}
:Played by: [[Ikusaburo Yamazaki]] 
:A rakugo storyteller known for his freestyle brand of rakugo. His actual birth name is never specified, but Kikuhiko used to call him by the diminutive {{Nihongo|"Shin"|信}}. He was given the name "'''Hatsutaro'''" when he became a student of the Seventh Generation Yakumo. Later on, he would change his name to "'''Sukeroku'''". Despite his talent for rakugo, Yakumo refused to pass on his name to him due to the rebellious nature of his rakugo.  Following a heated argument, he was expelled from the school. He would move to the countryside to marry Miyokichi and start a family where he would spend his life drinking away in depression until Kikuhiko arrived to bring him back to doing rakugo again. He and Miyokichi died when they fell from a balcony in an inn where Sukeroku gives his last performance with Kikuhiko.
;{{Nihongo|Third Generation Sukeroku Yurakutei|三代目 有楽亭 助六|Sandaime Yūrakutei Sukeroku}} / {{Nihongo|Yotaro|与太郎|Yotarō}} / {{Nihongo|Kyoji|強次|Kyōji}} 
:{{anime voices|[[Tomokazu Seki]]}}
:Played by: [[Ryō Ryūsei]] 
:An aspiring storyteller who was recently released from prison. He was born "'''Kyoji'''" and was given the name "'''Yotaro'''" when he became a student. Having been a big admirer of Kikuhiko's rakugo he decides to become his student. His desire to inherit Sukeroku's name that leads to conflicts between him and Yakumo due to Yakumo not wanting his brand of rakugo to be corrupted. Ten years after being accepted by Yakumo, he is promoted to a shin'uchi and formally becomes the '''Third Generation Sukeroku Yurakutei'''.
;{{Nihongo|Miyokichi|みよ吉}} / {{Nihongo|Yurie|ユリエ}}
:{{anime voices|[[Megumi Hayashibara]]}}
:Played by: [[Aya Ōmasa]]
:A young woman who worked as a Geisha who first appeared as the Seventh Generation Yakumo's mistress whom he met in Manchuria. She became attracted to Kikuhiko due to his aloof personality and the two developed an on-again-off-again relationship. Eventually Kikuhiko rejected her and out of spite she began a relationship with Sukeroku which resulted in her becoming pregnant with their daughter, Konatsu. Sukeroku and Miyokichi eventually left for the countryside after Sukeroku's expulsion. However, she did not care for Sukeroku or Konatsu and instead turned to prostitution to earn money. After Kikuhiko appeared and rejected her advances again, she attempted suicide, but Sukeroku convinced her to stop. However, she slipped from a balcony and in his attempt to save her, both Miyokichi and Sukeroku fell to their deaths. However the actual cause of her death was revealed much later in the series. Her true given name was "'''Yurie'''".
;{{Nihongo|Konatsu|小夏}}
:{{anime voices|[[Yu Kobayashi]]}}
:Played by: [[Riko Narumi]] 
:Sukeroku's and Miyokichi's daughter. She learned her father's style of rakugo to entertain customers at a soba shop in the countryside. Following the death of her parents, Kikuhiko became her legal guardian. She holds a great deal of resentment for Kikuhiko as she initially believed he was responsible for her father's death, and more recently because he represents the 'old-fashioned' traditional rakugo that does not allow women to participate. She later gave birth to a child named Shinnosuke whose biological father's identity is not yet revealed. Later in the series, it was revealed that she had witnessed the death of Sukeroku and Miyokichi but had lost her memories of the incident.

===Supporting characters===
;{{Nihongo|Eisuke Higuchi|樋口 栄助|Higuchi Eisuke}}
:{{anime voices|[[Toshihiko Seki]]}}
:A popular writer who is interested in helping Yotaro in writing new rakugo. In his youth, he had crushes and admiration on Miyokichi. This eventually extended to his obsession with Yakumo whom he had even seek to become his apprentice.
;{{Nihongo|Matsuda|松田}}
:{{anime voices|[[Shigeru Ushiyama]]}}
: Matsuda is Yakumo's retainer and driver. He has been employed by the Yakumos since the Seventh Generation.
;{{Nihongo|Fourth Generation Mangetsu Tsuburaya|四代目 円屋 萬月|Yondaime Tsuburaya Mangetsu}}
:{{anime voices|[[Koji Yusa]]}}
:Yotaro's fellow storyteller from Kyoto. He had stopped performing rakugo for some time after his father's death.
;{{Nihongo|Seventh Generation Yakumo Yurakutei|七代目 有楽亭 八雲|Nanadaime Yūrakutei Yakumo}}
:{{anime voices|[[Hiroshi Yanaka]]}}
:A famous storyteller and Kikuhiko's and Sukeroku's teacher.
;{{Nihongo|Amaken|アマケン}}
:{{anime voices|[[Kappei Yamaguchi]]}}
: Rakugo critic and fan of Yakumo. His father Amano was a literary critic. Amaken is disliked by Yakumo.
;{{Nihongo|Ani-san|アニさん}}
:{{anime voices|Shou Sudou}}
;{{Nihongo|Bansai Tsuburaya|円屋 萬歳|Tsuburaya Bansai}}
:{{anime voices|[[Chafurin]]}}
;{{Nihongo|Shinnosuke|信之助}}
:{{anime voices|[[Mikako Komatsu]]}} (child) / [[Yūki Ono]]
:Konatsu's son who greatly admires Yakumo's rakugo. Yotaro believes the father to be the boss of the gang that he once belonged to. However, it is heavily suggested that Shinnosuke is Konatsu's son with Yakumo.
;{{Nihongo|Koyuki|小雪}}
:{{anime voices|[[Ayaka Asai]]}}
:Konatsu and Yotaro's daughter.

==Media==

===Manga===
The manga series written and illustrated by Haruko Kumota began its serialization in the ''ITAN'' magazine published by [[Kodansha]] from March 25, 2010, to June 7, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-04-06/showa-genroku-rakugo-shinju-manga-ends-on-june-7/.100732|title=Shōwa Genroku Rakugo Shinjū Manga Ends on June 7|date=6 April 2016|website=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=18 November 2016}}</ref> The manga has been compiled in ten ''[[tankōbon]]'' volumes, with the first volume being published on July 7, 2011,<ref name="RS1"/> and the tenth and final volume being published on September 7, 2016.<ref name="RS10"/> [[Kodansha USA]] licensed the manga for release in North America, with the first volume scheduled to publish on May 23, 2017.<ref name="DS1"/>

