'''Miley Save Fuzzy''' is a [[website]] in which an anonymous [[Miley Cyrus]] fan threatened to kill and eat their pet [[cat]] unless she returns to [[Twitter]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mileysavefuzzy.com |title=Will Miley save Fuzzy? |publisher=Mileysavefuzzy.com |date= |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Matyszczyk |first=Chris |url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-17852_3-10387620-71.html |title=Miley Cyrus: Twitter should be banned &#124; Technically Incorrect - CNET News |publisher=News.cnet.com |date=2009-10-30 |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://perezhilton.com/2009-10-29-crazed-fans-threatens-miley-return-to-twitter-or-the-cat-gets-eaten |title=Crazed Fans Threatens: Miley, Return To Twitter Or The Cat Gets Eaten! |publisher=Perez Hilton |date=2009-10-29 |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://oceanup.com/2009/10/28/girl-threatens-to-kill-a-cat-unless-miley-cyrus-reopens-her-twitter-account|title=Girl Threatens To Kill A CAT Unless Miley Cyrus Reopens HER TWITTER Account|work=oceanup.com|accessdate=22 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://celebrities.ninemsn.com.au/blog.aspx?showcomments=true&blogentryid=526562 |title=Miley fan: "Return to Twitter or my cat gets it!" - Your daily fix of celebrity gossip |publisher=Celebrities.ninemsn.com.au |date= |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Miley Cyrus |url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b151536_miley_cyrus_secret_husband_cops_plea.html |title=Miley Cyrus' "Secret Husband" Cops a Plea |publisher=E! Online |date=2009-10-30 |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref> Miley Cyrus is aware of the campaign, and commented about it in several interviews,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mileysavefuzzy.com/response.html |title=Will Miley save Fuzzy? - Miley's Response |publisher=Mileysavefuzzy.com |date=2009-11-25 |accessdate=2012-10-28}}</ref><ref>[http://www.mileycyrus.com/2009/11/11/sweeet-interview-with-miley/ ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100518194701/http://www.mileycyrus.com/2009/11/11/sweeet-interview-with-miley/ |date=May 18, 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=3 november 2009 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sL2XVeOx-YU |title=Miley Cyrus Interview from mileyworld (Halloween) |publisher=YouTube |date=2009-11-03 |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=10 november 2009 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sXGYZsqKlOU |title=Miley Cyrus on Sweeet! Radio |publisher=YouTube |date=2009-11-10 |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5g9daNQxtHM |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-11-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305003503/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5g9daNQxtHM |archivedate=2016-03-05 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0XnkIKTUaxQ |title=Nikolina interviews Miley Cyrus |publisher=YouTube |date=2009-11-16 |accessdate=2012-10-28}}</ref> in which she stated that she will not come back to Twitter.
==MileySaveFuzzy.com== The website was created on October 24, 2009. On the website, the anonymous fan claimed that if Miley Cyrus did not come back to Twitter by November 16 (a deadline which was later extended to November 22<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mileysavefuzzy.com/updates.html |title=Will Miley save Fuzzy? - Updates |publisher=Mileysavefuzzy.com |date=2009-11-25 |accessdate=2012-10-28}}</ref>), their cat, Fuzzy, would be killed and eaten. The fan claimed this action is legal in their country. The website includes several pictures of Fuzzy, as well as a cat [[recipe]]s section.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mileysavefuzzy.com/recipes.html |title=Will Miley save Fuzzy? - Recipes |publisher=Mileysavefuzzy.com |date=2009-11-25 |accessdate=2012-10-28}}</ref>
On November 23, 2009, the Miley Cyrus fan posted a new update on the website, named ''Fuzzy's Demise'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mileysavefuzzy.com/demise.html |title=Will Miley save Fuzzy? - Fuzzy's Demise |publisher=Mileysavefuzzy.com |date=2009-11-25 |accessdate=2012-10-28}}</ref> claiming that the cat is dead. The fan claimed that the cat was taken to a clinic and was [[Animal euthanasia|euthanized]], and was later eaten. A very detailed explanation of the entire process is described, and pictures of a supposedly dead Fuzzy were posted.
Shortly after the update was announced, there were difficulties accessing the website. An error page showed up, presumably due to the large amount of hits it received, causing bandwidth issues.{{or|date=September 2012}}
==Public response and legitimacy== The website received media attention throughout the [[United States]] and in other countries, such as Spain,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.europapress.es/chance/gente/noticia-miley-cyrus-vuelves-twitter-mato-gato-20091030135408.html |title='Miley Cyrus, o vuelves a Twitter o mato a mi gato'. |publisher=Europapress.es |date=2009-10-30 |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ww2.eslamoda.com/chismes/?p=6745 |title=Eslamoda.com &#124; Chismes! Gossip Cotilleo * lo mejor de los famosos |publisher=Ww2.eslamoda.com |date=2009-11-06 |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref> Romania<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.acasatv.ro/rebelii-de-acasa/un-fan-al-lui-miley-cyrus-o-ameninta-ca-si-va-omori-pisica-daca-aceasta-nu-se-intoarce-pe-twitter.html |title=Un fan al lui Miley Cyrus o ameninta ca-si va omori pisica, daca aceasta nu se intoarce pe Twitter! |publisher=Acasatv.ro |date= |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref> and others. The campaign was also mentioned on various radio stations across the globe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.961kiss.com/pages/tallcathy.html?an=WTF-IS-WRONG-WITH-PEOPLE |title=96.1 Kiss |publisher=96.1 Kiss |date=2009-10-29 |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.973thehawk.com/showdj.asp?DJID=46684 |title=(Khki-Fm) |publisher=97.3 The Hawk |date= |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref>
People working against the site have contacted organizations such as [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]] and [[Humane Society of the United States|The Humane Society]], who responded on their official forums and by email, saying that nothing can be done, as no crime is being committed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mileysavefuzzy.com/updates.html |title=Will Miley save Fuzzy? - Updates |publisher=Mileysavefuzzy.com |date= |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://streetteam.peta2.com/public/folder_view.cfm?pageid=341&option=view_thread&postid=3176128&folderid=727 |title=PETA2 // Boards |publisher=Streetteam.peta2.com |date= |accessdate=2009-11-15}}</ref>
