[[Image:Toyama Museum of Modern Art.jpg|thumb|The Museum of Modern Art, Toyama]]
The {{nihongo|'''Museum of Modern Art, Toyama'''|富山県立近代美術館|Toyama Kenritsu Kindai Bijutsukan}} is a museum in [[Toyama, Toyama|Toyama]], [[Toyama Prefecture|Toyama]].  It is one of Japan's many museums which are supported by a prefecture.<ref>[[Louis-Frédéric|Nussbaum, Louis-Frédéric]]. (2005). [https://books.google.com/books?id=p2QnPijAEmEC&pg=PA671&dq= "Museums"] in ''Japan Encyclopedia'', pp. 671-673.</ref>  

The museum, which opened in 1981, stands within Jōnan Park in central Toyama. It displays a permanent collection and also temporary exhibitions.

