{{infobox Organization |name = Rede dos Emissores Portugueses |image = REP_logo.png |image_border = |size = 90px |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |abbreviation = REP |motto = "Associação Nacional de Radioamadores" ("National Association of Radio Amateurs") |formation = 1926<ref name="rep"/> |extinction = |type = [[Non-profit organization]] |status = |purpose = Advocacy, Education |headquarters = [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]] |location = |region_served = [[Portugal]] |membership = |language = [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] |leader_title = President |leader_name = Jose Carlos B. Nora CT1END |main_organ = |affiliations = [[International Amateur Radio Union]] |num_staff = |budget = |website = http://www.rep.pt/ |remarks = }}
The '''Rede dos Emissores Portugueses''' ('''REP''') (n [[English language|English]], '''Network of Portuguese Transmitters''') is a national [[non-profit organization]] for [[amateur radio]] enthusiasts in [[Portugal]]. REP was founded in 1926 by Eugenio de Avillez P1AE, an early Portuguese radio experimenter.<ref name="rep">Rede dos Emissores Portugueses (2008). [http://www.rep.pt/ Rede dos Emissores Portugueses] official web site. Retrieved Aug. 8, 2008.</ref> Key membership benefits of the REP include a [[QSL card|QSL]] bureau for those amateur radio operators in regular communications with other amateur radio operators in foreign countries, and the sponsorship of [[amateur radio operating award]]s and radio [[contesting|contests]]. The REP represents the interests of Portuguese amateur radio operators before Portuguese and international regulatory authorities. REP is the national member society representing Portugal in the [[International Amateur Radio Union]], which it joined in 1931.<ref name="iaru">International Amateur Radio Union (2008). [http://www.iaru.org/iaru-soc.html "Member Societies"]. Retrieved Aug. 1, 2008.</ref>
